8.9.19  7:09 am   Hi, Bill. i read that you said: "my secret is just live under a rock" regarding your style of content. in some media it's really hard to come up with anything original if you haven't at least got an overview of the surroundings, just so you don't unknowingly repeat someone else's idea. on the other hand, you've been creating for so long now, your stuff's been maturing in a unique barrel, so it's got to be original in some way or other. do you think being idiosyncratic and persistent enough is a good way to create original content?

     
also, is it really less reliable than "knowing the literature"? people will say "lone wolf runaway hits are very rare" but still, how likely are you to create something interesting by deducing your way to an idea after analyzing what everyone else has done? maybe there's a balance to strike here. i'd like to hear your thoughts. thanks
